# hexa-lang /.own — L1 project-local (8 rules)
# SSOT — 프로젝트 고유 절대 규칙. L0(/.raw) 와 병렬, 독립 id namespace.
# 포맷 스펙: self/raw_loader.hexa (L0 와 동일 문법)

own 1 convention "stage0 wrapper 경유"
  slug stage0-wrapper
  decl doc/hexa_lang_breakthroughs.json#HX8
  proof tool/rebuild_stage0.hexa
  why 2026-04-15 T63 재빌드 5-10초 × 자식 6-8 → xpcproxy 폭주 → kernel panic. tool/rebuild_stage0.hexa 만 경유 — 직접 flatten_imports → hexa_v2 → clang 체인 금지.

own 2 live "SELF-HOST 경로 전용"
  slug self-host-path
  enforce self/codegen_c2.hexa
  decl doc/hexa_lang_breakthroughs.json#HX7
  proof self/codegen_c2.hexa
  why 언어 기능 수정은 self/codegen_c2.hexa + self/runtime.c + self/interpreter.hexa + self/native/hexa_v2 경유만. 프리빌드 ./hexa 수정 금지.

own 3 live "AI-native SELF-FORMAT (.<attr>-rules.json)"
  slug ai-native-self-format
  enforce self/attrs/_registry.hexa#find_rules_helpers
  decl doc/hexa_lang_breakthroughs.json#HX11
  proof self/attrs/sealed.hexa
  why 모든 신규 @attr 은 프로젝트별 .<attr>-rules.json 양식 주입 지원. 하드코딩 섹션/상수 금지.

own 4 new "bt-solution-claim-ban — 7대난제 해결 주장 금지 + LLM 자체 검증판단 금지"
  slug bt-solution-claim-ban
  enforce tool/llm_verdict_guard.hexa
  decl tool/llm_verdict_guard.hexa
  scope LLM output 이 파일/commit msg/.raw-audit/.roadmap/ROADMAP.md 에 기록되는 verdict claim. 7대난제 "해결" 선언 포함.
  proof tool/llm_verdict_guard.hexa
  why LLM 의 "verified/passed/satisfied/완료/성공/검증됨/확인됨/통과" 류 선언은 증거 아님. 검증 = 물리(Landauer kT·ln2/FLOPs/latency) ∨ 수학(Brent/Banach/JSD/Frob/cos/K(G|S₀)) ∨ 코드(hexa tool 실행 output + commit SHA) 중 최소 1 동반 필수. seed C structural co-occurrence ±8 line window. raw#10 proof-carrying 을 LLM output 축으로 구체화.
  follow-up raw 32 llm-no-self-judgment new → warn 승급 30-day streak
  follow-up airgenome/hooks/post_tool.hexa 에 guard inject

own 5 new "cli-via-hx-install — external CLI configuration requires hx install (direct entry invocation banned)"
  slug cli-via-hx-install
  enforce tool/own_cli_install_lint.hexa
  scope Patterns in scripts / docs / config that directly invoke the entry path of a registry-listed package (run.hexa / cli/run.hexa / bin/hive / launch.hexa / build/yoga-cli and the like) declared in tool/pkg/registry.tsv. Scanned extensions: *.hexa *.sh *.md *.json *.plist *.yml.
  proof tool/own_cli_install_lint.hexa
  why Direct invocation bypasses the hx shim at ~/.hx/bin/<name>, so (a) `hx update` cannot propagate registry changes to callers, (b) a registry entry column change produces silent caller drift, (c) hardcoded paths break on repo or environment relocation. Routing through `hx install <name>` and then `<name> <command>` makes tool/pkg/registry.tsv the single source of truth and lets one `./hexa tool/hx.hexa update` synchronise the whole ecosystem. Bypass: add a `hx-install-ignore` comment on the offending line (audited).

own 6 new "launchd-recurring-tasks — every hexa-lang launchd plist declared here with bounded timeout"
  slug launchd-recurring
  enforce tool/loop_lint.hexa
  scope Every ~/Library/LaunchAgents/*.plist whose ProgramArguments point at a hexa-lang-repo tool (absolute path under this repo or a `cd <repo>` wrapper) must be declared here as an own-N entry with keys: interval, cmd, owner (plist absolute path), timeout, proof, why. Absorbs the launchd portion of raw#17 scope — .loop retained for non-launchd recurring tasks (cron, ScheduleWakeup, RemoteTrigger) until raw#17 is consolidated.
  proof tool/loop_lint.hexa
  why 2026-04-21 fork-storm incident: 108 user.safe_hexa.* zombie launchd jobs had accumulated, and roadmap-watcher (60s cadence) plus readme-english-audit (15m) were running unregistered. roadmap_critical_path --selftest stuck 10+ min was re-spawned every 60s, piling up 1722 stage0 processes and nearing kernel panic. Declaration here with a required `timeout` key enforces a per-tick time budget (grammar-level @bounded(N) equivalent) so a stuck tick is killed before the next launchd fire pile-up. Cross-check by tool/loop_lint.hexa scans the LaunchAgents directory and matches each hexa-lang plist against an own `owner` key.
  follow-up tool/loop_lint.hexa --scan-launchd flag extended to emit remediation diff (add `owner` line or `launchctl unload` candidate) instead of bare violation list.
  follow-up raw#17 consolidation — once this rule matures, raw#17 scope reduces to non-launchd recurring tasks only.

own 7 new "roadmap-watcher launchd job (60s)"
  slug loop-roadmap-watcher
  interval 60s
  cmd hexa run tool/roadmap_watcher.hexa
  owner ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.airgenome.roadmap-watcher.plist
  proof tool/roadmap_watcher.hexa
  timeout 45s
  enforce tool/loop_lint.hexa
  why Snapshots .roadmap progress per repo and restores .roadmap uchg + .raw-audit uappnd invariants. Stdout at /tmp/roadmap_watcher.stdout, stderr at /tmp/roadmap_watcher.stderr. Declared here under own#6 launchd-recurring so the shim becomes SSOT-visible.

own 8 new "readme-english-audit launchd job (15m)"
  slug loop-readme-english-audit
  interval 15m
  cmd hexa tool/readme_english_audit.hexa
  owner ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.need-singularity.readme-english-audit.plist
  proof tool/readme_english_audit.hexa
  timeout 300s
  enforce tool/loop_lint.hexa
  why Enforcement path for raw#33 ai-native-english-only across five need-singularity READMEs (CJK-mix detector). Declared here under own#6 launchd-recurring so the shim becomes SSOT-visible.
